{"questionId":"35029920","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A new concert hall was built with <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>14</mn></math> seats in the first row. Each subsequent row of the hall&nbsp;has two more seats than the previous row. The hall has a total of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn></math> rows.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Find:</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>the total number of seats in the concert hall.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>use of arithmetic series formula &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>14</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>52</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>20</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>660</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"35029920","referenceCode":"21M.2.SL.TZ2.3a.ii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"the total number of seats in the concert hall.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.2—Arithmetic sequences and series"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}